11:22.125 --> 11:24.167
"knocking on the door
and entering your room,

11:24.167 --> 11:26.334
"did it look like less
a violation

11:26.334 --> 11:28.501
and more like
an awkward mistake to you?"

11:28.501 --> 11:31.375
- To minimize the coat
and the door--

11:31.375 --> 11:33.459
just, like, a knock on the door

11:33.459 --> 11:35.584
doesn't really describe,
like, how I was feeling.

11:35.584 --> 11:36.834
- Mm-hmm.
- Because it was actually

11:36.834 --> 11:39.167
compounded
over the last two days.

11:39.167 --> 11:40.626
It wasn't an isolated thing.

11:40.626 --> 11:42.459
Had we had a productive
and constructive

11:42.459 --> 11:44.542
conversation
that first night...

11:44.542 --> 11:48.584
- I am not talking
about racial stereotypes.

11:48.584 --> 11:51.000
- Are you one of those people
that you don't see color?

11:51.000 --> 11:52.751
Tell me you're that girl.
"I don't see color."

11:52.751 --> 11:55.584
- I really don't see color.

11:55.584 --> 11:56.918
- It would have been like,

11:56.918 --> 11:58.501
"Wow, that was
such a learning thing."

11:58.501 --> 12:01.792
And then maybe the next night
with Kathy's drinking game,

12:01.792 --> 12:03.375
when I like nudged you,
we'd have been like,

12:03.375 --> 12:04.792
"Oh, like, we're like
girlfriends, but like--"

12:04.792 --> 12:06.334
- It was cumulative.
- It's cumulative.

12:06.334 --> 12:08.167
I can't change the way I felt.

12:08.167 --> 12:10.542
But I wish that we had
started off on the right foot

12:10.542 --> 12:12.042
because it would
have never happened.

12:12.042 --> 12:15.501
- I think the "violate" word
was very strong.

12:15.501 --> 12:17.876
You know,
I wasn't gonna let it go.

12:17.876 --> 12:19.709
- The word violation
actually means

12:19.709 --> 12:21.876
not respecting personal space,
which is how I felt.

12:21.876 --> 12:23.876
- Well, and it also means
violation of privacy.

12:23.876 --> 12:28.083
- Correct. Violation means
to abuse your privacy.

12:28.083 --> 12:30.417
- Boundaries.
- Disrespect of boundaries.

12:30.417 --> 12:31.959
Period. Google it.

12:31.959 --> 12:35.000
- That was inferring
that I was doing something

12:35.000 --> 12:37.125
directly to you to hurt you.

12:37.125 --> 12:38.792
- After Tahoe, Crystal,

12:38.792 --> 12:41.042
you admitted to having
an eating disorder.

12:41.042 --> 12:46.417
Did your body image issues
play into your feeling violated

12:46.417 --> 12:48.626
when she walked in
on you naked?

12:48.626 --> 12:50.042
- Without a doubt.

12:50.042 --> 12:54.125
My feeling of violation
was true to me.

12:54.125 --> 12:58.000
And it was disheartening that

12:58.000 --> 13:01.083
everyone was trying
to police my feelings.

13:01.083 --> 13:03.626
And so that's why
when we got back,

13:03.626 --> 13:05.584
I thought it was
really important to share

13:05.584 --> 13:08.792
with everyone my body
dysmorphia and eating disorder.

13:08.792 --> 13:12.042
- Did you speak to your mom
before the episode aired?

13:12.042 --> 13:13.751
- Yeah.
- Because she didn't know.

13:13.751 --> 13:16.292
- I knew she knew
I had food issues for sure.

13:16.292 --> 13:17.834
- What was her reaction?

13:17.834 --> 13:19.834
Um, she cried with me.

13:19.834 --> 13:21.292
She felt--don't make me cry.
- Aw.

13:21.292 --> 13:24.250
- Um, it was hard.

13:24.250 --> 13:27.876
It's hard for any parent
to experience that.

13:27.876 --> 13:29.501
But, you know, she's like,

13:29.501 --> 13:30.792
"Why do you want
to talk about it?"

13:30.792 --> 13:33.709
And I said,
"That's just who I am."

13:33.709 --> 13:35.959
And she just wants, like,
everything to be fine.

13:35.959 --> 13:37.000
- Okay.
- Right.

13:37.000 --> 13:38.417
- And, of course,
I tell her that

13:38.417 --> 13:39.709
even though
I struggle still.

13:39.709 --> 13:41.626
But it was positive in general,
for sure.

13:41.626 --> 13:44.918
- Abi Mendo tweeted,
"Crystal, you got mad at Sutton

13:44.918 --> 13:46.459
"and said, 'Please tell me
you're not that girl

13:46.459 --> 13:47.792
"that doesn't see color.'

13:47.792 --> 13:49.626
"And then it turned out
to be Kathy Hilton

13:49.626 --> 13:52.375
who's the one who said
she doesn't see color."

13:52.375 --> 13:53.918
- Michael Jackson and I
grew up together.

13:53.918 --> 13:57.000
And Michael said to me,
"Kathy, I don't see color."

13:57.000 --> 13:59.626
I said, "Well, either do we."

13:59.626 --> 14:03.792
- The conversation tone
was extremely different.

14:03.792 --> 14:05.334
You can't argue that.

14:05.334 --> 14:06.584
- In the two conversations?
- In the two conversations.

14:06.584 --> 14:07.876
- Right.
- Yes.

14:07.876 --> 14:10.083
It was nice to see
when that episode aired,

14:10.083 --> 14:13.083
you posted that apology
after your conversation.

14:13.083 --> 14:15.250
It's nice to see you
two worked it out.

14:15.250 --> 14:16.167
- It's nice.

14:16.167 --> 14:18.501
- Crystal, Alicia
from North Carolina said,

14:18.501 --> 14:19.834
"My heart broke when you shared

14:19.834 --> 14:21.834
your dad's
experience with racism."

14:21.834 --> 14:24.334
- I have been on
the other side of racism.

14:24.334 --> 14:25.918
I've been attacked.

14:25.918 --> 14:28.417
I remember I was in
the backseat of my dad's car.

14:28.417 --> 14:29.709
He was pumping gas.

14:29.709 --> 14:31.709
And there was a man
screaming at him,

14:31.709 --> 14:35.125
"Get out of my country.
You're taking all our money."

14:35.125 --> 14:37.709
- Why do you think he never
spoke about it with you?

14:37.709 --> 14:41.959
- You know, I think that's sort
of the classic Asian way.

14:41.959 --> 14:45.125
My dad was an immigrant.
He was particularly taught,

14:45.125 --> 14:47.542
"You're going to a new country.
You follow the rules.

14:47.542 --> 14:51.209
And if you want to be
successful, you just take it."

14:51.209 --> 14:55.000
But that particular story,
I remember his fear.

14:55.000 --> 14:58.417
I remember seeing, like,
he had got into--

14:58.417 --> 15:00.209
he just, like, got into the car
and drove so far,

15:00.209 --> 15:02.584
and we were only a block
from our house.

15:02.584 --> 15:06.292
And that was really sad to see.

15:06.292 --> 15:09.792
My dad was so...

15:09.792 --> 15:13.959
The goodness
of my dad was...beyond.

15:13.959 --> 15:16.375
And it was sad.

15:16.375 --> 15:18.000
And it's not a unusual story.

15:18.000 --> 15:19.083
- Right.

15:19.083 --> 15:23.250
Well, I was really upset
when I found out, Crystal,

15:23.250 --> 15:25.709
that you really
experienced threats

15:25.709 --> 15:27.959
and hate speech
directed at you

15:27.959 --> 15:31.417
as a result of being on
the show because you're Asian.

15:31.417 --> 15:32.959
What do you want
to say about that?

15:32.959 --> 15:34.125
- I haven't shared
with you guys.

15:34.125 --> 15:36.250
It's hundreds a day.

15:36.250 --> 15:37.501
- Wow.
- Still?

15:37.501 --> 15:39.125
- Still.

15:39.125 --> 15:42.292
- Saying yes to doing the show,
primarily, the reason

15:42.292 --> 15:46.876
was because I thought
Asians need representation.

15:46.876 --> 15:48.334
- Yeah.
- So when I got the call,

15:48.334 --> 15:49.667
I thought,
"You know what? Like,

15:49.667 --> 15:51.375
"what an incredible opportunity

15:51.375 --> 15:54.083
"for me to do that
to show my kids

15:54.083 --> 15:57.292
"and to speak out for people
who are too afraid,

15:57.292 --> 15:59.584
like my dad."
- Yeah.

15:59.584 --> 16:01.918
- You know, that was
my opportunity.

16:01.918 --> 16:06.959
So I thought,
"I'm gonna do it and...

16:06.959 --> 16:09.209
it's gonna be well received."
- Aw.

16:09.209 --> 16:11.918
- I'm just sorry for any part
that I played in that.

16:11.918 --> 16:14.167
- Thank you. I know.
- It's terrible.

16:14.167 --> 16:17.042
- It was so fun for me
and I think

16:17.042 --> 16:20.375
for the majority of people
watching to share your culture.

16:20.375 --> 16:22.042
I mean, you should feel
so great about it.

16:22.042 --> 16:23.125
- Yeah, you should.

16:23.125 --> 16:25.792
- And you shouldn't let
a percentage of assholes

16:25.792 --> 16:30.083
on social media define
not only your experience

16:30.083 --> 16:32.751
but the experience that
you put out there for others.

16:32.751 --> 16:34.501
- 100%.
- Absolutely.

16:34.501 --> 16:36.292
- I will say,
as much negativity

16:36.292 --> 16:37.751
has been out there,

16:37.751 --> 16:40.709
I am grateful
for every single person here,

16:40.709 --> 16:45.042
because everyone's been so open
and not only just accepting

16:45.042 --> 16:49.334
but, like, very excited
when I show my culture.

16:49.334 --> 16:52.876
And I'm obviously so proud
of my family and my background.

16:52.876 --> 16:55.959
And it's been a real pleasure.

16:55.959 --> 16:57.876
- I would love to hear from
any of the other women

16:57.876 --> 17:00.876
what you enjoyed
about getting to know Crystal.

17:00.876 --> 17:03.792
- I love going to her house
making dumplings.

17:03.792 --> 17:05.584
Garcelle and I ate so many.

17:05.584 --> 17:07.918
- Oh, my God.
- I had to roll myself home.

17:07.918 --> 17:09.709
- I may have done it.

17:09.709 --> 17:11.000
- Fantastic.

17:11.000 --> 17:12.792
- It's done. That's a dumpling.

17:12.792 --> 17:13.959
- I did a dumpling.

17:13.959 --> 17:17.042
- And the Chinese New Year
was so fun.

17:17.042 --> 17:20.042
[dramatic Chinese drum music]

17:20.042 --> 17:22.167
♪

17:22.167 --> 17:24.667
- And for me, Crystal's been
like a little sister

17:24.667 --> 17:26.000
a little bit.

17:26.000 --> 17:28.209
And I have loved what we have.

17:28.209 --> 17:29.584
I really have.
- That's great.

17:29.584 --> 17:31.209
- The aftermath
has been horrific.

17:31.209 --> 17:32.792
But with you guys,
it's been great,

17:32.792 --> 17:33.959
so I just want you
to know that.

17:33.959 --> 17:36.584
- On that note, we're gonna be
right back after this.

