26:42.417 --> 26:44.542
- It is so cute.

26:44.542 --> 26:46.959
- I love it.
- And chic. It really is.

26:46.959 --> 26:49.542
- Tell me the origin
of the box fan.

26:49.542 --> 26:50.542
- Mom.

26:50.542 --> 26:51.584
- Your mom?
- Oh!

26:51.584 --> 26:52.834
- And that's how I sleep.

26:52.834 --> 26:53.959
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

26:53.959 --> 26:55.626
- We all know that.
- She had a big standing one.

26:55.626 --> 26:57.083
- Is it the noise that--
- It's the hum.

26:57.083 --> 26:58.375
- Yeah, the hum.
- Our mom had one this big.

26:58.375 --> 26:59.209
- Like a helicopter.

26:59.209 --> 27:00.292
- This big in our room
and she had it

27:00.292 --> 27:02.501
at the foot of the bed,
and we all slept together.

27:02.501 --> 27:03.792
And it'd be--
[mimics fan humming]

27:03.792 --> 27:05.501
- Blowing on you?
- Yeah.

27:05.501 --> 27:07.083
- Oh, my gosh.

27:07.083 --> 27:08.792
- Nolan from Spokane said,

27:08.792 --> 27:11.000
"Kathy, what was it like
raising kids in a hotel

27:11.000 --> 27:14.042
when you lived
at the Waldorf Astoria?"

27:14.042 --> 27:15.125
- Very, very lovely.

27:15.125 --> 27:18.918
We loved being in close
quarters under one roof,

27:18.918 --> 27:22.626
except when Paris would sneak
out of the service elevator.

27:22.626 --> 27:26.083
- And how long did you
live there at the Waldorf?

27:26.083 --> 27:28.000
- Nine years.
- Nine years?

27:28.000 --> 27:29.167
- One day, I woke up

27:29.167 --> 27:31.292
and we couldn't find
Conrad and Alexia.

27:31.292 --> 27:33.876
And they were hiding
in an air conditioning vent...

27:33.876 --> 27:35.918
- What?
- At the Waldorf Astoria.

27:35.918 --> 27:37.209
- Terrifying.
- Crazy.

27:37.209 --> 27:38.042
- Yeah.

27:38.042 --> 27:40.334
- Every time you mention hotel,
I kind of lean in

27:40.334 --> 27:44.167
